Forms for 100(1-\alpha)\% CIs

Normal population with known \sigma: \overline{x} \pm z_{\alpha/2} \frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{m}}
Any population with unknown \sigma, when m large \overline{x} \pm z_{\alpha/2} \frac{s}{\sqrt{m}}
Normal population with unknown \sigma, m may be small \overline{x} \pm t_{\alpha/2, m-1} \frac{s}{\sqrt{m}}

Example (3/n)


Z = \frac{\overline{X} - \mu}{\sigma/ \sqrt{m}}
Assuming H_0 is true: Z = \frac{\overline{X} - 15}{\sigma/ \sqrt{m}}
But don’t know \sigma: Z = \frac{\overline{X} - 15}{S/ \sqrt{m}} \sim \mathsf{N}(0,1)
